# 2026-05-18 (A3/A4/A6): agent-runtime deps that were previously only baked
# into the Dockerfile via a separate RUN block. Bare-metal prod (no Docker)
# pip-installs from this file, so the Dockerfile-only path left A3/A4/A6
# agents broken in production. Moving them here makes pip the single source
# of truth: `pip install -r requirements.txt` covers every pip-installable
# runtime dep, OSS and prod both.
#   - coverage / pytest: coverage_runner shells out to `coverage run --branch
#     -m pytest`; ci_failure_reproducer re-runs failing pytest commands.
#   - checkov: hcl_terraform_analyzer invokes `checkov -d ... --output json`.
# Note: hadolint (A5) is a Go binary, not pip-installable — handle in the
# host-provision runbook. node + jest + go (also A6) are documented in
# docs/runbooks/runtime-prerequisites.md.
coverage>=7.0.0
pytest>=8.0.0
# pytest-asyncio: ci_failure_reproducer re-runs failing pytest invocations and
